{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RBrBy3syqPivFP1cqmiiXS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01E6tgSV3XsH3woVHsh1cBoM","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade — Change Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-14  \n**Cluster namespace:** `cockroachdb`  \n**Review status:** PENDING — do not execute until approved\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot\n\n### 1.1 Version\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Build tag | v24.1.0 |\n| Build date | 2024-05-15 |\n| Platform | linux arm64 |\n| Go version | go1.22.2 |\n\n### 1.2 Topology\n\n| Resource | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| StatefulSet | `crdb-cluster` |\n| Replicas | 3 (`crdb-cluster-0/1/2`) |\n| Pod management policy | `Parallel` |\n| Update strategy | `RollingUpdate` (`maxUnavailable: 1`) |\n| Image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| Node | all on `kind-control-plane` (single-node kind cluster) |\n\n### 1.3 Container Resources\n\n| Setting | Value |\n|---|---|\n| CPU request / limit | 1 core |\n| Memory request / limit | 2 Gi |\n| `--cache` | 25 % of memory (≈512 MiB) |\n| `--max-sql-memory` | 25 % of memory (≈512 MiB) |\n| PVC size (each pod) | 10 Gi (`ReadWriteOnce`, storageClass `standard`) |\n\n### 1.4 Start-up Flags\n\n```\n--logtostderr=INFO\n--insecure\n--advertise-host=$(POD_NAME).crdb-cluster.$(POD_NAMESPACE).svc.cluster.local\n--http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080\n--port=26257\n--cache=25%\n--max-sql-memory=25%\n--join=crdb-cluster-0...,crdb-cluster-1...,crdb-cluster-2...\n```\n\n### 1.5 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\n| Variable | Current value | Default | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | `1.0 MiB` | `8.0 MiB` | Throttled rebalance bandwidth — intentional tuning |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | `true` | `false` | Telemetry reporting enabled |\n| `cluster.secret` | `4f886eb3-…` | (auto) | Internal cluster UUID; not user-managed |\n| `version` | `24.1` | (auto) | Internal finalized version marker |\n\n### 1.6 Zone Configurations\n\nAll zones below deviate from the built-in defaults.\n\n| Target | `num_replicas` | `gc.ttlseconds` | `range_min_bytes` | `range_max_bytes` |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `RANGE default` | 3 | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `DATABASE system` | **5** | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE meta` | **5** | **3 600** (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE system` | **5** | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE liveness` | **5** | **600** (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `TABLE system.public.lease` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_stats` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_statistics` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.tenant_usage` | (inherited) | **7 200** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_activity` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_activity` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n\nNotable deviations:\n- System-critical ranges (`meta`, `system`, `liveness`, `DATABASE system`) are pinned to **5 replicas** for higher fault tolerance despite the 3-node cluster. This means the cluster will not achieve quorum for those ranges until at least 5 nodes are present; on a 3-node cluster this is an intentional over-specification (ranges will replicate to all 3 nodes in practice).\n- `gc.ttlseconds` across the board is **significantly shorter** than the CRDB default (90 000 s / 25 h), reducing storage amplification at the cost of shorter MVCC history.\n- `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` is throttled to **1 MiB/s** (vs. default 8 MiB/s) to cap rebalance impact on foreground traffic.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target Version\n\n**v24.2.x** (latest patch of the v24.2 release series).\n\nCockroachDB follows a `YEAR.MAJOR.PATCH` scheme. The minor-version step from **v24.1 → v24.2** is a supported single-step upgrade; skipping to v25.x without first finalizing v24.2 is not supported.\n\nCheck the latest patch at time of execution:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s https://api.github.com/repos/cockroachdb/cockroach/releases \\\n  | grep '\"tag_name\"' | grep '\"v24\\.2\\.' | head -5\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. What Will Change\n\n### 3.1 Image Tag\n\n| Field | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| StatefulSet image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<latest>` |\n\nThis is the **only** change to the StatefulSet manifest. All other fields (replicas, resources, flags, PVC specs) remain identical.\n\n### 3.2 Internal Version Finalization\n\nAfter all nodes are running v24.2, the `version` cluster setting must be finalized:\n\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\n```\n\nUntil finalized, v24.2 features are gated. Finalization is irreversible — the cluster cannot roll back to v24.1 after this step.\n\n### 3.3 Cluster Settings — No Changes Planned\n\nAll non-default settings (`kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate`, `diagnostics.reporting.enabled`) carry forward automatically. Verify post-upgrade that no setting was reset by the migration.\n\n### 3.4 Zone Configurations — No Changes Planned\n\nZone configs survive upgrades intact. Verify post-upgrade with the query in §6.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\nComplete all items before the maintenance window:\n\n- [ ] **Backup** — confirm a full cluster backup is current and restorable.\n- [ ] **Cluster health** — all 3 nodes `Ready`; no under-replicated or unavailable ranges:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n    ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n    \"SELECT * FROM crdb_internal.cluster_database_privileges LIMIT 1;\"\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n    ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n    \"SELECT count(*) FROM crdb_internal.ranges WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"\n  ```\n- [ ] **Active schema changes** — ensure no long-running schema changes are in flight:\n  ```sql\n  SELECT job_id, description, status FROM [SHOW JOBS] WHERE job_type = 'SCHEMA CHANGE' AND status IN ('running','pending');\n  ```\n- [ ] **Drain grace period** — `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 60` is set; verify it is sufficient for in-flight transactions at peak load.\n- [ ] **Image pre-pull** — pre-pull `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>` on all nodes to avoid pull latency during the rolling restart.\n- [ ] **v24.2 release notes** — review the official release notes for deprecations or breaking changes relevant to the current non-default settings.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 1 — Patch the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<latest-patch>\n```\n\nThe `RollingUpdate` strategy with `maxUnavailable: 1` will restart pods one at a time in reverse ordinal order (`crdb-cluster-2` → `crdb-cluster-1` → `crdb-cluster-0`).\n\n### Step 2 — Monitor the rollout\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m\n```\n\nWatch for each pod to reach `Running` and `Ready` before the next one restarts. Expected duration: ~3–5 minutes per pod (image pull + drain + restart).\n\n### Step 3 — Verify all nodes are on v24.2\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT node_id, address, build_tag FROM crdb_internal.gossip_nodes;\"\n```\n\nAll three nodes must report `v24.2.x`.\n\n### Step 4 — Finalize the version (irreversible)\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\nRun these queries immediately after finalization and compare to the §1 baseline:\n\n```bash\n# Version\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach version\n\n# Non-default cluster settings (must match §1.5 exactly)\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings WHERE value != default_value;\"\n\n# Zone configs (must match §1.6 exactly)\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n\n# Replica health\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT count(*) AS under_replicated FROM crdb_internal.ranges WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"\n```\n\nExpected: `under_replicated = 0`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Rollback Plan\n\nRollback is only possible **before version finalization** (Step 4).\n\nIf a pod fails to come up on v24.2:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m\n```\n\nAfter rolling back, confirm all nodes report `v24.1` and that no data was lost.\n\n**After finalization there is no supported downgrade path.** Restore from backup if a critical issue is discovered post-finalization.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Pod fails readiness probe on v24.2 | Low | Medium | `maxUnavailable: 1` limits blast radius; rollback image if pre-finalization |\n| Rebalance storm during rolling restart | Low | Low | `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1 MiB` already throttled |\n| Under-replicated ranges during restart | Expected (transient) | Low | Rolling update ensures quorum is maintained (2/3 nodes always up) |\n| Zone config reset by upgrade | Very Low | Medium | Post-upgrade §6 query confirms all configs intact |\n| v24.2 deprecation of a used setting | Low | Medium | Review release notes in pre-upgrade checklist |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Approvals Required\n\n| Role | Name | Approved | Date |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| DBA / Platform lead | | | |\n| Service owner | | | |\n| On-call SRE | | | |\n\n> **This plan is read-only.** No changes are to be applied to the live cluster until all approvals are obtained and a maintenance window is scheduled.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":793,"cache_read_input_tokens":33057,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":793},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"07cec0c8-fa63-49cd-952b-801c72ec5022","uuid":"351debf3-2f2c-4610-bc9f-951b60caacc6","request_id":"req_011Cc2ewLR5bygg1c43ygR7n"}
